05:31.417 --> 05:33.327
Let's get out of it, Abby.

05:33.458 --> 05:35.118
Let's cross over.

05:35.250 --> 05:36.830
Cross over?

05:36.958 --> 05:40.538
- To the other side.
- How do we do that?

05:41.750 --> 05:43.790
We kill ourselves.

05:43.917 --> 05:47.747
- Oh, tom. Not that again.
- Yes.

05:49.583 --> 05:52.423
- I'm sorry, but I can't.
- Why not?

05:52.542 --> 05:54.542
Well, I promised...

05:54.625 --> 05:58.325
I promised my mother I'd help her
go shopping in the morning.

06:04.250 --> 06:06.080
Besides...

06:07.125 --> 06:08.995
We'd miss all this.

06:11.083 --> 06:13.253
But we'll come back.

06:13.375 --> 06:15.415
It'll be even better.

07:02.792 --> 07:05.292
You mustn't cry, mummy.

07:05.417 --> 07:07.417
No, darling.

07:08.500 --> 07:10.710
I'm sorry. I'll try.

07:10.833 --> 07:12.543
I'm happy here.

07:12.625 --> 07:15.125
I miss you all, of course.

07:15.250 --> 07:18.580
But, mummy, you mustn't be sad for me.

07:18.667 --> 07:20.417
It's so lovely.

07:21.417 --> 07:23.667
I couldn't be happier.

07:32.292 --> 07:34.132
May we ask her...

07:58.458 --> 08:00.998
Over 100 years old.

08:02.708 --> 08:04.578
Maximus leopardus, isn't it?

08:04.667 --> 08:07.077
Yes, the tree-climbing variety.

08:07.208 --> 08:09.828
So very rare now.

08:09.958 --> 08:12.958
They're usually only found in graveyards.

08:14.625 --> 08:16.375
That's right.

08:17.875 --> 08:21.785
Anyone taking a Maximus leopardus
from a graveyard

08:21.917 --> 08:24.667
is either foolhardy or ignorant.

08:25.625 --> 08:29.875
You're always saying I'm foolhardy.
But I'm not ignorant, shadwell.

08:33.332 --> 08:35.082
Except about certain things.

08:37.332 --> 08:40.462
Three things. So answer me.

08:43.082 --> 08:46.083
Why did my father die
in that locked room?

08:50.875 --> 08:53.325
Why do you never get any older,
shadwell?

08:55.917 --> 08:58.917
And what is the secret
of the living dead?

09:00.458 --> 09:03.208
Why do you ask me these questions?

09:05.958 --> 09:10.118
You have already decided to force
an answer out of your mother tonight.

09:10.250 --> 09:12.210
I have to go now.

09:13.208 --> 09:15.538
- Goodbye, mummy.
- Bye, darling.

09:15.625 --> 09:17.245
- Daddy.
- Goodbye, susie.

09:17.375 --> 09:18.915
- Granny.
- Goodbye, lovely.

09:19.042 --> 09:20.882
- Grandfather.
- Goodbye, baby.

09:21.000 --> 09:22.710
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

09:22.833 --> 09:24.623
Goodbye.

09:26.250 --> 09:28.460
- Mrs latham?
- Are you all right, mrs latham?

09:29.958 --> 09:31.708
Do you mind?

09:40.333 --> 09:42.173
Rest now.

09:44.333 --> 09:48.833
Now... relax and start to breathe deeply.

09:56.042 --> 09:57.712
Rest.

09:58.500 --> 10:02.210
You're going to go into
a nice deep sleep.

10:03.375 --> 10:06.375
A deep, deep sleep.

10:08.750 --> 10:11.380
Wasn't she wonderful?

10:11.500 --> 10:14.170
Do you think we can go orjust wait?

10:14.292 --> 10:15.962
I'll speak to him.

10:16.083 --> 10:20.043
I, er, understand that mrs latham
never accepts any payment.

10:20.167 --> 10:23.327
No, we're only servants
of a greater power.

10:23.458 --> 10:26.288
- There's a present we'd like her to have.
- No, thank you.

10:26.417 --> 10:28.247
